fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.processor

Class AbstractATLProcessor<Q extends MogwaiQuery>

  • Object
    • AbstractQueryProcessor<Q>
      • AbstractATLProcessor<Q>
  • Type Parameters:
    Q - the kind of MogwaiQuery this processor supports
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ATLQueryProcessor, OCLQueryProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractATLProcessor<Q extends MogwaiQuery>
extends AbstractQueryProcessor<Q>
    An ATL-based processor that uses an internal ATL transformation to create the GremlinScript to compute.

    This class defines methods ATL-based processors have to implement, and default implementations integrating ATL options.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:

      • process

        public QueryResult process(Q query,
                           List<ModelDatastore> datastores,
                           Map<String,Object> options)
        Computes a query on the provided datastores with the given options.

        This method is internally called by all the process methods. Override it to change the processing algorithm of the processor.

        Adds an initialization step in the query processing that handles ATL-specific options.
